stimulusHtml:
• For the graph of the function f, the x axis ranges from negative 6 to 6 in increments of 1.
  • The y axis ranges from negative 6 to 6 in increments of 1. 
  • The graph is a line passing through (negative 5 comma negative 5), the origin, and (5 comma 5).
  • For the graph of the function g, the x axis ranges from negative 6 to 6 in increments of 1.
  • The y axis ranges from negative 6 to 6 in increments of 1.
  • The graph is a line passing through (negative 5 comma 5), the origin, and (5 comma negative 5).
     

 

  • For the graph of the function h, the x axis ranges from negative 6 to 6 in increments of 1.
  • The y axis ranges from negative 6 to 6 in increments of 1.
  • The graph is a horizontal line with a y value of 1.
  • For the graph of the function k, the x axis ranges from negative 6 to 6 in increments of 1.
  • The y axis ranges from negative 6 to 6 in increments of 1.
  • The graph is a horizontal line with a y value of 0.

 

​The function p{"digitSeparatorsAsMN":"auto"} (not shown) is a polynomial function of degree 3{"digitSeparatorsAsMN":"auto"}. The graphs of four functions f{"digitSeparatorsAsMN":"auto"}, g{"digitSeparatorsAsMN":"auto"}, h{"digitSeparatorsAsMN":"auto"}, and k{"digitSeparatorsAsMN":"auto"} are given. 

The output values of p{"digitSeparatorsAsMN":"auto"} are the same as the output values of the composition function when p{"digitSeparatorsAsMN":"auto"} is composed with one of these functions as the input function. For which of the functions is this statement true?
